        <h3>Critical Food Temperature Check</h3>
        <p>Regardless of whether dry ice is present, the most important safety step is checking your food's temperature if it's not completely frozen upon arrival.</p>
        <ul class="temperature-steps">
          <li><strong>SAFE: 40°F (4.4°C) or Less</strong><br>If the internal temperature is 40°F or below, your food is safe. Place it in the refrigerator or freezer immediately.</li>
          <li><strong>UNSAFE: Above 40°F (4.4°C)</strong><br>If the temperature is above 40°F, please DO NOT consume the food. For your safety, dispose of the meals.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

